  "prompt": "How did Elon Musk learn software engineering?",
  "response": "Elon Musk is largely self-taught in software engineering. As a child, he developed an interest in computing and technology. At the age of 10, he taught himself computer programming, and by the age of 12, he had created a video game called \"Blastar,\" which he sold to a computer magazine for approximately $500. Musk's approach to learning software engineering involved a combination of self-study, hands-on experimentation, and practical application.\n\nThroughout his career, Musk has continued to rely on self-directed learning and problem-solving skills, which have been crucial to his success in founding and leading technology-driven companies such as Zip2, PayPal, SpaceX, and Tesla. His ability to dive deep into technical areas and learn on the fly has been a hallmark of his entrepreneurial journey.",
